Open CL Kernel First compiled using the
aoc --board de5net_a7 --1x-clock-for-local-mem --sw-dimm-partition --opt-arg -fp-relaxed=true --opt-arg -fpc=true vadd.cl

aoc --board  p385a_hpc_ax115 --1x-clock-for-local-mem --sw-dimm-partition --opt-arg -fp-relaxed=true --opt-arg -fpc=true vadd.cl
command line option. This takes a long time!

ocl program then compiled using 
g++  vecadd_ocl.cpp -fPIC -I/opt/altera14.1/hld/host/include  -L/opt/altera14.1/hld/board/terasic/de5net/linux64/lib -L/opt/altera14.1/hld/host/linux64/lib  -lalteracl -ldl -lacl_emulator_kernel_rt  -lalterahalmmd -lterasic_apb_14.1_mmd -lelf -lrt -lstdc++ -o vecadd_ocl
command line option.

The included Make file should also work.
